dc_title_s: LiDAR-Derived Classified LAS (County Delivery) for Dane County, WI 2010
dc_description_s: This data represents LiDAR-derived classified LAS points for Dane County, Wisconsin in 2010. Point classification uses semi-automated techniques on the point cloud to assign the feature type associated with each point. LiDAR points can be classified into a number of categories including bare earth or ground, top of canopy, and water. The different classes are defined using numeric integer codes in the LAS files.
